Data provenance
---------------
These files re-distribute or are derived from previously published and
public-domain sources. Credit the original compilers when you use them. The
tabular files are provided as plain CSVs containing only the fields used by the
analysis (no unused sheets or columns).

  - data/raw/PFGData_sherds.csv, data/raw/PFGData_types.csv,
    data/raw/pfg-cpl-frequency.csv, data/raw/mainfort-pfg-cpl.csv,
    data/raw/mainfort-pfg-cplXY.txt
        Decorated-ceramic type counts (and type attributes) from the Lower
        Mississippi Survey of Phillips, Ford, and Griffin (1951), as digitized
        for this and prior work.
  - data/LMVData-22March2006.csv, data/LMVData_locations.csv
        Lower Mississippi Valley site attributes and locations (mound metrics,
        UTM coordinates, period assignments) compiled from the Lower
        Mississippi Survey site files.
  - data/raw/williams1954_cmv_counts.tsv, data/processed/williams1954_cmv_coords.tsv
        Southeast-Missouri survey assemblages and site locations from
        Williams (1954), digitized from the survey tables.
  - data/raw/14CDatesFromMainfort2001.csv
        Central-valley radiocarbon determinations compiled by Mainfort (2001).
  - data/CMV/*, data/Shapefiles/*
        Geospatial reference layers (Lower Mississippi Survey grid and
        hydrology/geology base layers). Site coordinates derive from public
        USGS topographic maps and the Lower Mississippi Survey site files.

